      <h2>What are Fixed Deposits?</h2>

      <p>
        A Fixed Deposit (FD) is one of the safest investment options available.
        You invest a lump sum for a fixed period at a pre-decided interest rate,
        and receive guaranteed returns at maturity.
      </p>

      <p>
        FDs are designed for capital protection rather than aggressive growth.
        They are widely used by individuals who prefer stability, predictability,
        and peace of mind over high-risk returns.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Minimal risk, especially with banks and post offices</li>
        <li><strong>Guaranteed Returns:</strong> Interest rate is fixed at the time of investment</li>
        <li><strong>Capital Protection:</strong> Your principal remains secure</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-muted">
        FDs form the foundation of a conservative investment strategy.
      </p>
    </div>

